          </details>

          <details class="group border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-lg p-4">
            <summary class="font-label font-bold text-on-surface cursor-pointer">Should I use antistatic bubble wrap for jewelry?</summary>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm mt-3 leading-relaxed">Standard bubble wrap is fine for most jewelry. Antistatic wrap is more important for electronics. For watches with electronic movements, consider antistatic as an extra precaution.</p>
          </details>

          <details class="group border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-lg p-4">
            <summary class="font-label font-bold text-on-surface cursor-pointer">What bubble wrap size works for different jewelry types?</summary>
